Accessing OpenStreetMap data with R

The original article was published on dominicroye

Open Street Maps包含了街道、高速公路、医院等位置信息.

首先安装必须的程序库.

#install the osmdata, sf, tidyverse and ggmap package
if(!require("osmdata")) install.packages("osmdata")
if(!require("tidyverse")) install.packages("tidyverse")
if(!require("sf")) install.packages("sf")
if(!require("ggmap")) install.packages("ggmap")

#load packages
library(tidyverse)
library(osmdata)
library(sf)
library(ggmap)

查询数据

查看可用OSM特征数据

#the first five features
head(available_features())
[1] "4wd only"  "abandoned" "abutters"  "access"    "addr"      "addr:city"
#amenities
head(available_tags("amenity"))
[1] "animal boarding" "animal shelter"  "archive"         "arts centre"     "atm"            
[6] "baby hatch"     
#shops
head(available_tags("shop"))
[1] "agrarian"  "alcohol"   "anime"     "antiques"  "appliance" "art"

检索数据

使用 getbb() 来创建指定地方的地理范围.opq() 用于构建查询语句. add_osm_feature( ) 用于实施过滤条件.

#building the query
q <- getbb("Madrid")%>%
  opq()%>%
  add_osm_feature("amenity", "cinema")

str(q) #query structure

用 osmdata_*( ) 发送检索命令到服务器, 然后返回相应格式的数据.

cinema <- osmdata_sf(q)

可视化数据

检索得到的sf对象可以在ggplot2中使用geom_sf()直接显示. 另外可以使用ggmap的get_map()下载地图背景.

#our background map
mad_map <- get_map(getbb("Madrid"),maptype = "toner-background")

#final map
ggmap(mad_map)+
  geom_sf(data=cinema$osm_points,
          inherit.aes =FALSE,
          colour="#238443",
          fill="#004529",
          alpha=.5,
          size=4,
          shape=21)+
  labs(x="",y="")

找到指定范围内的超市

#bounding box for the Iberian Peninsula
m <- matrix(c(-10,5,30,46),ncol=2,byrow=TRUE)
row.names(m) <- c("x","y")
names(m) <- c("min","max")

#building the query
q <- m %>% 
      opq (timeout=25*100) %>%
         add_osm_feature("name","Mercadona")%>%
         add_osm_feature("shop","supermarket")

#query
mercadona <- osmdata_sf(q)

#final map
ggplot(mercadona$osm_points)+
  geom_sf(colour="#08519c",
          fill="#08306b",
          alpha=.5,
          size=1,
          shape=21)+
  coord_sf(datum=NA)+
  theme_void()
